tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    version_id INT,
    experiment_date DATE,
    result VARCHAR(100),
    FOREIGN KEY (version_id) REFERENCES version_tracking(version_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT NOT NULL,
    model_id INT NOT NULL,
    result_value FLOAT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ExperimentResults (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT NOT NULL,
    result FLOAT NOT NULL,
    experiment_date DATE,
    notes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Experiments (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    experiment_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    started_at TIMESTAMP,
    ended_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE ModelVersionExperiments (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_version_id INT NOT NULL,
    experiment_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_version_id) REFERENCES ModelVersions(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES Experiments(id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
    result_value FLOAT,
    experiment_date DATE,
    model_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE model_history (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    version_number INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    last_updated_at TIMESTAMP
);
